{"query": "As an alternative to increasing turbine cut-in speeds, what other operational changes can reduce bat mortality at wind farms?", "summary": "As alternatives to increasing turbine cut-in speeds, several operational changes can reduce bat mortality at wind farms. Preventing turbine blades from turning at low wind speeds ('feathering') has been shown effective, with five of six studies in the USA and Canada finding that feathering resulted in fewer bat fatalities than at conventionally operated turbines (Action 970). Slowing the rotation of turbine blades at low wind speeds is another alternative, with one replicated, randomized, controlled study in Canada finding that bat fatalities were reduced when turbine blades were slowed at low wind speeds (Action 2939). 

Automatically reducing turbine blade rotation when bat activity is high has proven effective, with two studies in Germany and the USA showing that automatically reducing rotation speed when bat activity is predicted to be high resulted in fewer bat fatalities for all bat species combined and for five bat species (Action 971). Deterring bats from turbines using ultrasound shows mixed results, with three studies in the USA finding varied effectiveness - one study found 21-51% fewer bats killed in the first year but mixed results in the second year, while other studies found ultrasonic deterrents reduced fatalities for some but not all bat species (Action 968). 

Additional operational modifications include applying textured coating to turbines, though one study in the USA found this did not reduce bat activity or observations (Action 1957). Several other potential operational changes lack sufficient research evidence, including removing turbine lighting to reduce bat and insect attraction (Action 969), deterring bats using low-level ultraviolet light (Action 1958), minimizing road lighting to reduce insect attraction (Action 1969), and closing off potential access points on turbines to prevent roosting bats (Action 972).", "action_ids": ["970","2939","971","968","1957","969","1958","1969","972"]}

